# Cesium Globe Integration

The 3D globe lives in `features/cesium-globe/`. Cesium is loaded dynamically via `loadCesium()` from `~/utils/cesium-loader` -- never import it statically.

## Using the CesiumViewer Component

```typescript
import { CesiumViewer } from '~/features/cesium-globe';
```

```vue
<CesiumViewer
    ref="cesiumRef"
    container-id="my-viewer"
    :initial-view="{ longitude: -73.9, latitude: 40.7, height: 500000 }"
    @ready="onViewerReady"
    @click="onGlobeClick"
    @error="onError"
/>
```

The component exposes these methods via template ref:

- `flyTo(longitude, latitude, height?)` -- animate camera to position
- `addEntity(options)` -- add a Cesium entity, returns the entity
- `clearEntities()` -- remove all entities
- `viewer` -- readonly ref to the raw `Cesium.Viewer` instance

## Depending on the Globe from Another Module

```typescript
export default defineFeatureModule({
    id: 'my-feature',
    requires: ['useCesiumViewer'],
    // ...
});
```

## Key Details

- Requires authentication -- the viewer won't initialize without a logged-in user
- Cesium Ion token is read from `runtimeConfig.public.cesiumAccessToken`
- Falls back to OpenStreetMap tiles if no Ion token is provided
- The module exposes a global entity store at `window.__cesiumGlobeStore` for cross-module persistence
